  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing emergency multisector assistance in response to displacement crisis in Marib governorate, Yemen</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In response to the critical needs resulting from the escalation in violence in Marib, IOM is providing a multisectoral humanitarian response in 24 sites &#x2013; across Camp Coordination and Camp Management (CCCM), Water, Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH), Protection, Emergency Shelter/Non-Food Items (ESNFI) and Health sectors and the rapid response mechanism (RRM), including multi-purpose cash (MPC). The agency provides at least one form of assistance in 35 additional sites in Ma&#x2019;rib, in coordination with other humanitarian partners &#x2013; including 11 sites which are managed by IOM and where service provision is coordinated/provided by other humanitarian partners. The project targets a total of 108,062 affected people with its CCCM engagement, 7,616 with Protection, 6,000 with MPC, 22,800 with WASH and 77,399 with Health activities respectively.</narrative>
  </description>
